; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures timer2 and generates a periodic interrupt based on external clock source.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Connecting target port with a suitable instrument.
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. Timer2
;    2. SCUCLK
;    3. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. Timer20 : PA4/PA4 (Output/Capture Input)
;               : PA5 (External Clock Input)
;    2. PCU     : PD4 (Clock Output)
;
; E. Port Connection
;    1. PD4 (Clock Output) ----> PA5 (Timer20 External Clock Input)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; Timer20
; 1. Channel                   : 0 (Timer20)
;
; 2. Clock                     : [ 0 e f 0 ]
;    Source                    : e (External Clock Input) 
;    External Clock Input Edge : f (Falling) 
;    Timer2 Pre-Divide         : 0 (No Pre-Divider available so default 0)
;
; 3. Config                    : [ 0 i p h 40000 40000 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    Mode                      : p (Periodic)
;    Output Port Polarity      : h (High)
;    A Data                    : 40000
;    B Data                    : 40000
;
; PCU
; 1. Port Group                : 5 (PCU Port F) / 2 (PCU Port C)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 5 4 a 1 ] [ 2 2 a 1 ]
;    Pin Number                : 4 / 2
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 1 (Clock Output) / 1 (EC20)
;
; SCUCLK
; 1. Clock Out                 : [ clkout w 0 e ]  
;    Clock Source              : w (MCLK - WDTRC 40KHz)
;    Clock Source Divide       : 0 (Clock Source 2^N)
;    Clock Output Enable       : e (Enable)
;
; PCU (PD4)
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 3 4 a 4'
mpause 30

; PCU (PA5)
sendln 'port 0 5 a 4'
mpause 30

; SCUCLK
sendln 'cm scuclk'
mpause 30
sendln 'clkout w 0 e'
mpause 30

; Timer20
sendln 'cm timer2'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'clk 0 e f 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 0 i p h 40000 40000'
mpause 30
sendln 'log on'
mpause 30
sendln 'start 0'
